---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import '../styles/rules.css';
---

<Layout title="Scoring Rules">
  <main class="rules-page">
    <header class="page-header">
      <h1>📋 Scoring Rules</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Understand how points are calculated for your predictions</p>
    </header>

    <div class="rules-content">
      <section class="rules-section">
        <h2>Tournament Structure</h2>
        <p>
          Football tournaments are structured with an initial group stage or round-robin phase,
          followed by a second round of final quadrangular groups before determining the best team in the tournament.
        </p>
        <p>
          For all matches, users can predict the result. The objective is to correctly predict
          the match outcome and earn points.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="rules-section">
        <h2>Prediction Rules</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>You can change your prediction up to a maximum of <strong>10 minutes before</strong> the match start date and time.</li>
          <li>
            The prediction only includes the <strong>90 MINUTES</strong> of regular time plus (+) stoppage time
            given by the referee, but <strong>EXCLUDES</strong> any extra time (2 × 15 minutes) or penalty shootout results.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="rules-section">
        <h2>Scoring System</h2>
        <p>
          For each match, you can make a prediction of the result (example: Brazil 2 – Germany 1).
          In each match, you can accumulate points according to the following rules:
        </p>

        <h3>For predicting the result (winner or draw)</h3>
        <div class="example-box">
          <p>
            <strong>5 points in the first round and 10 in knockout stages</strong>
          </p>
          <p>
            If you correctly predict the winning team or a draw, you will earn 5 points in the first round
            or 10 points in knockout stages. For example, if your prediction was 2–1 and the match ended 1–0,
            you will earn 5 points for getting the result right (in the first round). The same applies if the
            match ends 2–2 and your prediction was 0–0.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h3>For predicting the number of goals for each team</h3>
        <div class="example-box">
          <p>
            <strong>2 points in the first round and 4 in knockout stages</strong>
          </p>
          <p>
            If you correctly predict the number of goals scored by each team, for example, if the match
            ends 2–1 and your prediction was 0–1, you earn 2 points for correctly predicting the away team's goals.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h3>For predicting the goal difference</h3>
        <div class="example-box">
          <p>
            <strong>1 point in the first round and 2 in knockout stages</strong>
          </p>
          <p>
            If the match ends 3–1 and your prediction was 2–0, you will earn 1 or 2 points for correctly
            predicting the goal difference.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="rules-section">
        <h2>Scoring Summary</h2>
        <table class="scoring-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Category</th>
              <th>First Round</th>
              <th>Knockout Stages</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>Correct result (winner/draw)</td>
              <td><span class="points-value">5</span> points</td>
              <td><span class="points-value">10</span> points</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Correct home team goals</td>
              <td><span class="points-value">2</span> points</td>
              <td><span class="points-value">4</span> points</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Correct away team goals</td>
              <td><span class="points-value">2</span> points</td>
              <td><span class="points-value">4</span> points</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Correct goal difference</td>
              <td><span class="points-value">1</span> point</td>
              <td><span class="points-value">2</span> points</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><strong>MAX TOTAL</strong></td>
              <td><strong>10 points</strong></td>
              <td><strong>20 points</strong></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <p>
          The standings table will reflect the accumulated score and the registration/join date to the group,
          shown in the last column. Within each group, tiebreakers may include factors such as the highest
          number of matches with full or partial scores (10 points, 7 points, 6 points, 5 points).
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="rules-section">
        <h2>Examples</h2>

        <h3>Example 1: Perfect Prediction (1:0 → 1:0)</h3>
        <p>If your prediction was 1:0 and the match ended 1:0, you will earn:</p>
        <table class="scoring-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Category</th>
              <th>First Round</th>
              <th>Knockout Stages</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>Correct result (winner)</td>
              <td>5 points</td>
              <td>10 points</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Correct home team goals</td>
              <td>2 points</td>
              <td>4 points</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Correct away team goals</td>
              <td>2 points</td>
              <td>4 points</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Correct goal difference</td>
              <td>1 point</td>
              <td>2 points</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="highlight-row">
              <td><strong>TOTAL</strong></td>
              <td><strong>10 points</strong></td>
              <td><strong>20 points</strong></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>

        <h3>Example 2: Partial Match (2:0 → 3:1)</h3>
        <p>If your prediction was 2:0 and the match ended 3:1, you will earn:</p>
        <table class="scoring-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Category</th>
              <th>First Round</th>
              <th>Knockout Stages</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>Correct result (home team wins regardless of score)</td>
              <td>5 points</td>
              <td>10 points</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Correct home team goals</td>
              <td>0 points</td>
              <td>0 points</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Correct away team goals</td>
              <td>0 points</td>
              <td>0 points</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Correct goal difference (2 goals)</td>
              <td>1 point</td>
              <td>2 points</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="highlight-row">
              <td><strong>TOTAL</strong></td>
              <td><strong>6 points</strong></td>
              <td><strong>12 points</strong></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </section>
    </div>

    <nav class="back-nav">
      <a href="/">← Back to Home</a>
      <a href="/predictions">Make Predictions →</a>
    </nav>
  </main>
</Layout>